api/en/geometries/extrudegeometry:
[page:BufferGeometry] â†’ <h1 id="extrudegeometry" class=" section-header"><span class="descname">ExtrudeGeometry</span></h1> <p class="section-desc">Creates extruded geometry from a path shape.</p> <iframe id="scene" src="https://threejs.org/docs/scenes/geometry-browser.html#ExtrudeGeometry"></iframe>  <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="code-example">Code Example</h2>
<pre data-language="javascript"><code>
		const length = 12, width = 8;

		const shape = new THREE.Shape();
		shape.moveTo( 0,0 );
		shape.lineTo( 0, width );
		shape.lineTo( length, width );
		shape.lineTo( length, 0 );
		shape.lineTo( 0, 0 );

		const extrudeSettings = {
			steps: 2,
			depth: 16,
			bevelEnabled: true,
			bevelThickness: 1,
			bevelSize: 1,
			bevelOffset: 0,
			bevelSegments: 1
		};

		const geometry = new THREE.ExtrudeGeometry( shape, extrudeSettings );
		const material = new THREE.MeshBasicMaterial( { color: 0x00ff00 } );
		const mesh = new THREE.Mesh( geometry, material ) ;
		scene.add( mesh );
		</code></pre> </div> <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="constructor">Constructor</h2>
<h3 id="extrudegeometry-array-shapes-object-options-" class=" section-header">
<span class="descname">ExtrudeGeometry</span>(<span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Array</span> <code class="sig-name">shapes</code></span>, <span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Object</span> <code class="sig-name">options</code></span>)</h3> <p> shapes â€” Shape or an array of shapes. <br> options â€” Object that can contain the following parameters. </p> <ul> <li> curveSegments â€” int. Number of points on the curves. Default is <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">12</span></code>. </li> <li> steps â€” int. Number of points used for subdividing segments along the depth of the extruded spline. Default is <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">1</span></code>. </li> <li>depth â€” float. Depth to extrude the shape. Default is <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">1</span></code>.</li> <li> bevelEnabled â€” bool. Apply beveling to the shape. Default is true. </li> <li> bevelThickness â€” float. How deep into the original shape the bevel goes. Default is <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">0.2</span></code>. </li> <li> bevelSize â€” float. Distance from the shape outline that the bevel extends. Default is bevelThickness - 0.1. </li> <li> bevelOffset â€” float. Distance from the shape outline that the bevel starts. Default is <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">0</span></code>. </li> <li>bevelSegments â€” int. Number of bevel layers. Default is <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">3</span></code>.</li> <li> extrudePath â€” THREE.Curve. A 3D spline path along which the shape should be extruded. Bevels not supported for path extrusion. </li> <li>UVGenerator â€” Object. object that provides UV generator functions</li> </ul> <p>This object extrudes a 2D shape to a 3D geometry.</p> <p> When creating a Mesh with this geometry, if you'd like to have a separate material used for its face and its extruded sides, you can use an array of materials. The first material will be applied to the face; the second material will be applied to the sides. </p> </div> <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="properties">Properties</h2>
<p>See the base <a class="reference internal" href="buffergeometry"><code class="xref js js-buffergeometry">BufferGeometry</code></a> class for common properties.</p> <h3 id="parameters-object" class=" section-header"><dt class="sig sig-object js">
<span class="sig-name descname">parameters</span><span class="sig-colon">:</span> <span class="sig-type">Object</span>
</dt></h3> <p> An object with a property for each of the constructor parameters. Any modification after instantiation does not change the geometry. </p> </div> <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="methods">Methods</h2>
<p>See the base <a class="reference internal" href="buffergeometry"><code class="xref js js-buffergeometry">BufferGeometry</code></a> class for common methods.</p>   </div><div class="_attribution">
  <p class="_attribution-p">
    &copy; 2010&ndash;2025 Three.js Authors<br>Licensed under the MIT License.<br>
    <a href="https://threejs.org/docs/api/en/geometries/ExtrudeGeometry.html" class="_attribution-link">https://threejs.org/docs/api/en/geometries/ExtrudeGeometry.html</a>
  </p>
</div>

api/en/geometries/lathegeometry:
[page:BufferGeometry] â†’ <h1 id="lathegeometry" class=" section-header"><span class="descname">LatheGeometry</span></h1> <p class="section-desc"> Creates meshes with axial symmetry like vases. The lathe rotates around the Y axis. </p> <iframe id="scene" src="https://threejs.org/docs/scenes/geometry-browser.html#LatheGeometry"></iframe>  <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="code-example">Code Example</h2>
<pre data-language="javascript"><code>
		const points = [];
		for ( let i = 0; i &lt; 10; i ++ ) {
			points.push( new THREE.Vector2( Math.sin( i * 0.2 ) * 10 + 5, ( i - 5 ) * 2 ) );
		}
		const geometry = new THREE.LatheGeometry( points );
		const material = new THREE.MeshBasicMaterial( { color: 0xffff00 } );
		const lathe = new THREE.Mesh( geometry, material );
		scene.add( lathe );
		</code></pre> </div> <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="constructor">Constructor</h2>
<h3 id="lathegeometry-array-points-integer-segments-float-phistart-float-philength-" class=" section-header"> <span class="descname">LatheGeometry</span>(<span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Array</span> <code class="sig-name">points</code></span>, <span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Integer</span> <code class="sig-name">segments</code></span>, <span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Float</span> <code class="sig-name">phiStart</code></span>, <span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Float</span> <code class="sig-name">phiLength</code></span>) </h3> <p> points â€” Array of Vector2s. The x-coordinate of each point must be greater than zero. Default is an array with (0,-0.5), (0.5,0) and (0,0.5) which creates a simple diamond shape.<br> segments â€” the number of circumference segments to generate. Default is 12.<br> phiStart â€” the starting angle in radians. Default is <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">0</span></code>.<br> phiLength â€” the radian (0 to 2PI) range of the lathed section 2PI is a closed lathe, less than 2PI is a portion. Default is 2PI. </p> <p>This creates a [name] based on the parameters.</p> </div> <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="properties">Properties</h2>
<p>See the base <a class="reference internal" href="buffergeometry"><code class="xref js js-buffergeometry">BufferGeometry</code></a> class for common properties.</p> <h3 id="parameters-object" class=" section-header"><dt class="sig sig-object js">
<span class="sig-name descname">parameters</span><span class="sig-colon">:</span> <span class="sig-type">Object</span>
</dt></h3> <p> An object with a property for each of the constructor parameters. Any modification after instantiation does not change the geometry. </p> </div> <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="methods">Methods</h2>
<p>See the base <a class="reference internal" href="buffergeometry"><code class="xref js js-buffergeometry">BufferGeometry</code></a> class for common methods.</p>   </div><div class="_attribution">
  <p class="_attribution-p">
    &copy; 2010&ndash;2025 Three.js Authors<br>Licensed under the MIT License.<br>
    <a href="https://threejs.org/docs/api/en/geometries/LatheGeometry.html" class="_attribution-link">https://threejs.org/docs/api/en/geometries/LatheGeometry.html</a>
  </p>
</div>

api/en/geometries/shapegeometry:
[page:BufferGeometry] â†’ <h1 id="shapegeometry" class=" section-header"><span class="descname">ShapeGeometry</span></h1> <p class="section-desc"> Creates an one-sided polygonal geometry from one or more path shapes. </p> <iframe id="scene" src="https://threejs.org/docs/scenes/geometry-browser.html#ShapeGeometry"></iframe>  <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="code-example">Code Example</h2>
<pre data-language="javascript"><code>
		const x = 0, y = 0;

		const heartShape = new THREE.Shape();

		heartShape.moveTo( x + 5, y + 5 );
		heartShape.bezierCurveTo( x + 5, y + 5, x + 4, y, x, y );
		heartShape.bezierCurveTo( x - 6, y, x - 6, y + 7,x - 6, y + 7 );
		heartShape.bezierCurveTo( x - 6, y + 11, x - 3, y + 15.4, x + 5, y + 19 );
		heartShape.bezierCurveTo( x + 12, y + 15.4, x + 16, y + 11, x + 16, y + 7 );
		heartShape.bezierCurveTo( x + 16, y + 7, x + 16, y, x + 10, y );
		heartShape.bezierCurveTo( x + 7, y, x + 5, y + 5, x + 5, y + 5 );

		const geometry = new THREE.ShapeGeometry( heartShape );
		const material = new THREE.MeshBasicMaterial( { color: 0x00ff00 } );
		const mesh = new THREE.Mesh( geometry, material ) ;
		scene.add( mesh );
		</code></pre> </div> <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="constructor">Constructor</h2>
<h3 id="shapegeometry-array-shapes-integer-curvesegments-" class=" section-header">
<span class="descname">ShapeGeometry</span>(<span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Array</span> <code class="sig-name">shapes</code></span>, <span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Integer</span> <code class="sig-name">curveSegments</code></span>)</h3> <p> shapes â€” <a class="reference internal" href="array"><code class="xref js js-array">Array</code></a> of shapes or a single <a class="reference internal" href="shape"><code class="xref js js-shape">shape</code></a>. Default is a single triangle shape.<br> curveSegments - <a class="reference internal" href="integer"><code class="xref js js-integer">Integer</code></a> - Number of segments per shape. Default is 12. </p> </div> <div class="section">
<h2 class="section-title section-header" id="properties">Properties</h2>
