<span class="sig-name descname">load</span><span class="sig-paren">(</span><span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type"><span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">String</span></span> <code class="sig-name"><span class="sig-name">url</span></code></span></span><span class="sig-paren">, </span><span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type"><span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Function</span></span> <code class="sig-name"><span class="sig-name">onLoad</span></code></span></span><span class="sig-paren">, </span><span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type"><span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Function</span></span> <code class="sig-name"><span class="sig-name">onProgress</span></code></span></span><span class="sig-paren">, </span><span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type"><span class="sig-param"><span class="sig-type">Function</span></span> <code class="sig-name"><span class="sig-name">onError</span></code></span></span><span class="sig-paren">)</span><span class="sig-returns"><span class="sig-colon">:</span> <span class="sig-type">undefined</span></span>
</dt> </h3> <p> <a class="reference internal" href="string"><code class="xref js js-string">url</code></a> â€” the path or URL to the file. This can also be a <a class="reference external" href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/Data_URIs">Data URI</a>.<br> <a class="reference internal" href="function"><code class="xref js js-function">onLoad</code></a> â€” Will be called when load completes. The argument will be the loaded <a class="reference internal" href="image"><code class="xref js js-image">image</code></a>.<br> <a class="reference internal" href="function"><code class="xref js js-function">onProgress</code></a> (optional) â€” This callback function is currently not supported.<br> <a class="reference internal" href="function"><code class="xref js js-function">onError</code></a> (optional) â€” Will be called when load errors.<br> </p> <p> Begin loading from url and return the <a class="reference internal" href="imagebitmap"><code class="xref js js-imagebitmap">image</code></a> object that will contain the data. </p> <h3 id="this-setoptions-object-options-" class=" section-header"><dt class="sig sig-object js" id="setOptions">
